/* gamedata-w7-research.mjs — Research Grid (W7 minehead-adjacent grid puzzle) supplementary
 * data: grid TOOLS, observation pool, farming sticker table, node-unlock/Glimbo-trade table, and
 * Minehead's separate "BonusQTY" reward track. Extracted verbatim from N.js. GENERATED by a
 * one-off extraction script (scratchpad, not committed); refresh after a major patch.
 *
 * SCOPE — what this file does NOT duplicate: bonuses/research.mjs already owns RES_GRID_COEFF
 * (per-node % bonus coefficients for the ids it has verified), RES_OCCURRENCE_PCT (== Research[5]
 * below, re-confirmed not re-exported), gridAllmulti(), gridBonus(), gridLevel(). Import from
 * that file, don't copy its exports. This file only adds what it doesn't have.
 *
 * *** HEADLINE FINDING — the "~240-node grid table" the priority brief asked for DOES NOT EXIST
 * AS STATIC DATA. *** `Ya.ResGridSquares=function(){return[...]}` (N.js byte 13994134) is a
 * 240-row literal where EVERY row is byte-for-byte identical: `["Name","1","1","0","0","desc"]`.
 * This is a compile-time PLACEHOLDER/default, not per-node content — confirmed by cross-checking
 * against the UI code that reads it (N.js byte ~12793459, `ResGridSquares[nodeIdx][0]` for the
 * displayed name and `[5]` for the description): if the literal were the real data every node
 * would display literally "Name" / "desc" in-game, which is not what players see. The 240 node
 * identities/effects must be assigned into `CustomLists.h.ResGridSquares` at RUNTIME, either
 * procedurally per-account or from a resource not embedded in N.js as a JS literal (an external
 * asset load, or server-side generation — not resolvable by reading this client file). PRACTICAL
 * UPSHOT: there is no static "node -> effect" table to extract; bonuses/research.mjs's existing
 * approach (verify each RES_GRID_COEFF id against a REAL SAVE's displayed text, one at a time) is
 * the only viable path, and is already the right design — this file does not attempt to add more
 * ids to that table (no way to derive them without a save to read against). Do not spend more
 * time looking for a static grid table in N.js; there isn't one.
 *
 * GRID TOOLS — the magnifier lenses + grid shapes players place on the grid (separate from the
 * per-node bonuses). Ya.Research()=function(){return[...]}, N.js byte 13960475 (`return[` at
 * 13960502..13973608), a 40-row CustomLists.Research MEGA-LITERAL shared across Research Grid,
 * Minehead, Farming stickers, and Glimbo (each sub-table documented at its own row below; the
 * literal itself is one giant `return[...]`, not 40 separate functions).
 *   Research[3]  (10) shape names            Research[4]  (10) shape effect templates
 *   Research[5]  (10) occurrence-slot % — ALREADY bonuses/research.mjs's RES_OCCURRENCE_PCT,
 *                     re-verified here byte-identical: [25,15,50,20,20,35,25,30,35,60]
 *   Research[6]  (14) magnifier/shape unlock flavor text (per Research-skill-level unlock, not
 *                     itself a numeric table)
 *   Research[7]  (3)  lens type names: "Magnifying_Glass","Optical_Monocle","Kaleidoscope"
 *   Research[8]  (3)  lens type descriptions (EXP lens / insight lens / adjacency-power lens)
 *
 * OBSERVATIONS — the "...head" mob pool players roll into their Observation slots. Research[11]
 * (32 names) / Research[12] (32 tier ids, 0-4) / Research[10] (32, a display-order permutation,
 * not gameplay data — omitted). savemap/w67.mjs documents Spelunk idx 9 as this list's OWNED
 * copy... actually the accurate cross-reference is Research idx 11 ("observations list (length
 * feeds Grid_Bonus 67/68/107)") — this file supplies the POOL those observations are drawn from,
 * not the save's owned-list (that's savemap's job, unchanged here).
 *
 * FARMING STICKERS — extends bonuses/research.mjs's inline comment ("Farming/sticker nodes...").
 * Research[23] (12 names) / Research[24] (12 descriptions) / Research[25] (12 coeffs). Only 7 are
 * real (ids 0-6); ids 7-11 are literal "Nonexistent_Sticker" filler (row-count gotcha: the save
 * array Research[9] is 12 slots wide but only 7 can ever be non-zero).
 *
 * GRID-NODE UNLOCK REQUIREMENTS == GLIMBO'S TRADE TABLE (the SAME 22-row table serves both
 * systems — confirmed by reading both consumers, not assumed):
 *   Research[26] (22) grid node ids that need a special unlock (not just points) to appear
 *   Research[27] (22) the unlock/trade item's name (e.g. "Refinery3", "Critter7A", "Quest110")
 *   Research[28] (22) cost GROWTH rate (Glimbo_Cost's geometric base)
 *   Research[29] (22) 0/1 flag (meaning not traced further; left verbatim, not guessed)
 * Glimbo_Cost(b), N.js byte 10919446, verbatim (SAVE Research[12][b] = trade-count for slot b —
 * a DIFFERENT "Research[12]" than CustomLists.Research[12] above; save key vs CustomLists key,
 * same name, disambiguated by which `getGameAttribute` call wraps it in the source):
 *   raw = (1 + Research[12][b] + 1.5*Research[12][b]) * Math.pow(CustomLists.Research[28][b], Research[12][b])
 *         * Math.max(.1, 1 - 25*Summoning("EventShopOwned",38,0)/100)
 *   cost = raw < 1e9
 *     ? Math.floor(Math.max(1, raw * Math.max(.2, 1 - Companions(57)/100)))
 *     : raw
 * Glimbo_CanAfford(b) = ItemsAndStorageOWNED[Research[27][b]] >= Glimbo_Cost(b) ? 1 : 0
 * GlimboTotalTrades() = round(sum(SAVE Research[12][f] for f in 0..Research[27].length-1))
 * GlimboDRmulti() = Grid_Bonus(168,0) >= 1 ? 1 + Grid_Bonus(168,2)/100 : 1   // "Drop Rate TRUE
 *   Multi per 100 Glimbo Trades" (node 168 not in RES_GRID_COEFF; not re-derived here)
 *
 * MINEHEAD BonusQTY — a SEPARATE Minehead reward track from bonuses/minehead.mjs's Button_Bonuses
 * (that one buckets OptLacc[594] button presses; this one is a flat unlock-tier list). Extends
 * bonuses/minehead.mjs's MINEHEAD_QTY (currently only id 8). Research[19] (32 descriptions,
 * "Nothing..._yet..." padding for ids 23-31) / Research[20] (32 coeffs — cross-checked: id 8 =
 * "2", EXACT match to the existing MINEHEAD_QTY[8]=2 entry). Formula unchanged from
 * bonuses/minehead.mjs's docstring: `Minehead("BonusQTY",b,0) = Research[7][4] > b ?
 * CustomLists.Research[20][b] : 0` (Research[7][4] = SAVE Research row 7, "research progress/AFK
 * state" per savemap — a tier counter, not this file's CustomLists.Research[7] lens-name row;
 * again same top-level name, different object).
 * -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */

